## 🎯 Key Takeaways from Management Feedback

### Critical Quotes

> **Danielle:** "Show them, don't tell them. Don't explain the ontology - show them the results."

> **Sudhanshu:** "What will Suresh say to his boss about BSS Magic? That's what creates the pipeline."

> **Danielle:** "You're accelerating revenue, not just fixing tickets."

> **Sudhanshu:** "The demo needs to plant the next seed in their head - they're building a digital twin."

### The Wrong Approach ❌
- Starting with "let me explain the ontology"
- Showing technical screens without context
- Focusing on "we fixed data corruption"
- Treating it as a better ticketing system

### The Right Approach ✅
- Start with "we scanned your system and found this..."
- Show business impact first (revenue, time, cost)
- Frame as "digital twin" / "process intelligence"
- Create contrast: current state → desired state
- Let them ask "how did you do that?" → then show ontology

